# Node Template — environment configuration
#
# You normally DON'T need this file. On first run the app asks for your AI key
# IN THE BROWSER and saves it here for you (and you can change it any time from
# the "API key" button) — no hand-editing. This file is only for advanced or
# headless setups where you want to pre-seed the key.

# ─── Local AI key (the app writes this for you via the browser) ────
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# ─── Optional ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI_PROVIDER=anthropic       # leave unset to auto-detect from whichever key is set
# MODEL=claude-opus-4-7       # override the default model
# PORT=3000                   # override the HTTP port

# ─── Hosted-only (set on the box, never in a local install) ────────
# When this Node runs online, the runtime supplies JWT_SECRET (must match the
# tracker), DATABASE_URL, and a shared ANTHROPIC_API_KEY. You normally don't set
# those here.
#
# If your Node later calls an external API, add the pattern here: a
# SERVER-MANAGED token, hosted-only, with a graceful native fallback when absent.
# Example:
# SOME_PROVIDER_TOKEN=
